orded as being borne by the elder sister of Moses (Exodus 15:20). Since the names of both Moses and his brother Aaron are probably of Egyptian origin, it is possible that this female name is too. It was enthusiastically taken up as a given name by the Israelites, and is still found mainly, but by no means exclusively, as a Jewish name."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margareta","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margarete","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margrethe","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]},{"name":"\"Ana\"","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Hebrew.  See  <b>Anne</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Miriam Margareta \"Ana\" Tarnova Of Wallachia was born about 1281, in Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Romania. She married Prince Vlaicu Ivancu Basarab of Valachia Walachei about 1310. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1281–":"umbes 1281–Surnud","1270–1352":"1270–1352","1302–1367":"1302–1367","1310–1364":"1310–1364","1281–Female":"1281–Surnud","       1302":"1302","1302":"1302","1367":"1367","ABT 1310":"umbes 1310","1310":"1310","1364":"1364","1352":"1352","Abt 1281":"umbes 1281","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Rumänien":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Rumeenia","Curtea De Arges,Arges,Romania":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Rumeenia","Of, Curtea-De-Arges, Arges, Romania":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Rumeenia"},"fi":{"Abt 1281–":"noin 1281–Kuollut","1270–1352":"1270–1352","1302–1367":"1302–1367","1310–1364":"1310–1364","1281–Female":"1281–Kuollut","       1302":"1302","1302":"1302","1367":"1367","ABT 1310":"noin 1310","1310":"1310","1364":"1364","1352":"1352","Abt 1281":"noin 1281","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Rumänien":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Romania","Curtea De Arges,Arges,Romania":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Romania","Of, Curtea-De-Arges, Arges, Romania":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Romania"},"fr":{"Abt 1281–":"environ 1281–Décédée","1270–1352":"1270–1352","1302–1367":"1302–1367","1310–1364":"1310–1364","1281–Female":"1281–Décédée","       1302":"1302","1302":"1302","1367":"1367","ABT 1310":"environ 1310","1310":"1310","1364":"1364","1352":"1352","Abt 1281":"environ 1281","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Rumänien":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Roumanie","Curtea De Arges,Arges,Romania":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Roumanie","Of, Curtea-De-Arges, Arges, Romania":"Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Roumanie","lifeSummary":"Lady Miriam Margareta \"Ana\" Tarnova Of Wallachia est née environ 1281, à Curtea de Argeş, Argeş, Ro